import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import scipy.stats as stats


# Pastikan data memiliki kolom 'stag' untuk waktu dan 'event' untuk data tersensor
time = data['Days']
event = data['Status']

# Langkah 2: Mendefinisikan fungsi untuk membuat probability plot
def probability_plot(data, dist_name, ax):
    if dist_name == 'lognorm':
        shape, loc, scale = stats.lognorm.fit(data, floc=0)  # fit dengan floc=0 untuk lognorm
        params = (shape, loc, scale)
    else:
        dist = getattr(stats, dist_name)
        params = dist.fit(data)

    # Menggunakan distribusi yang sesuai dengan parameter yang diperoleh
    (osm, osr), (slope, intercept, r) = stats.probplot(data, dist=dist_name, sparams=params, plot=ax)
    ax.set_title(f'{dist_name.capitalize()}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Days')
    ax.set_ylabel('Percent')
    ax.grid(True)

    # Hitung kolmogorov-smirnov statistic
    ks_stat, p_value = stats.kstest(data, dist_name, args=params)
    ax.text(0.5, 0.9, f'KS Stat: {ks_stat:.2f}\n(p-value: {p_value:.2f})',
            horizontalalignment='center', verticalalignment='center',
            transform=ax.transAxes, bbox=dict(facecolor='white', alpha=0.8))

# Langkah 3: Menyiapkan plot
fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(12, 10))

# Membuat plot untuk berbagai distribusi
distributions = ['weibull_min', 'lognorm', 'expon', 'norm']
for dist_name, ax in zip(distributions, axs.flatten()):
    probability_plot(time[event == 1], dist_name, ax)  # hanya menggunakan data yang tidak tersensor

# Menambahkan judul besar
fig.suptitle('Probability Plot for Days', fontsize=16)

# Menampilkan plot
plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.03, 1, 0.95])
plt.show()

from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline
from sksurv.ensemble import RandomSurvivalForest

rsf.fit(X_train, y_train)

In[]:
lower, upper = np.percentile(y['t.tdm'], [10, 90])
times = np.arange(lower, upper + 1)
In[]:
rsf_surv_prob = np.row_stack([fn(times) for fn in rsf.predict_survival_function(X_test)])
In[]:
random_surv_prob = 0.5 * np.ones((y_test.shape[0], times.shape[0]))
In[]:
from sksurv.functions import StepFunction
from sksurv.nonparametric import kaplan_meier_estimator
In[]:
km_func = StepFunction(*kaplan_meier_estimator(y_test['e.tdm'], y_test["t.tdm"]))
km_surv_prob = np.tile(km_func(times), (y_test.shape[0], 1))
In[]:
score_brier = pd.Series(
    [
        integrated_brier_score(y, y_test, prob, times)
        for prob in (rsf_surv_prob, random_surv_prob, km_surv_prob)
    ],
    index=["RSF", "Random", "Kaplan-Meier"],
    name="IBS",
)

pd.concat((score_cindex, score_brier), axis=1).round(3)

    as_concordance_index_ipcw_scorer,

gcv_iauc = GridSearchCV(
    as_cumulative_dynamic_auc_scorer(rsf_data, times=times),
    param_grid=cv_param_grid,
    cv=cv,
    n_jobs=4,
).fit(X, y)
In[]:
def plot_grid_search_results(gcv, ax, name):
    ax.errorbar(
        x=gcv.cv_results_["param_estimator__max_depth"].filled(),
        y=gcv.cv_results_["mean_test_score"],
        yerr=gcv.cv_results_["std_test_score"],
    )
    ax.plot(
        gcv.best_params_["estimator__max_depth"],
        gcv.best_score_,
        "ro",
    )
    ax.set_ylabel(name)
    ax.yaxis.grid(True)


_, axs = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(6, 6), sharex=True)
axs[-1].set_xlabel("max_depth")

plot_grid_search_results(gcv_cindex, axs[0], "c-index")
plot_grid_search_results(gcv_iauc, axs[1], "iAUC")
plot_grid_search_results(gcv_ibs, axs[2], "$-$IBS")
